⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Kefka Palazzo
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Kefka Palazzo:FF6:94fd5d⟧

WHO   — Kefka Palazzo — the god of ruin
WHAT  — The principal antagonist of Final Fantasy VI — a cackling, nihilistic jester turned living weapon turned god, who poisons kingdoms, betrays his Emperor, and topples the world into the World of Ruin to reign over a meaningless creation from atop his tower.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the experiments that made him a weapon also unmade the man, leaving only the will to destroy; because he can find no meaning in a broken world and so resolves to erase all meaning from it; because if nothing can be loved, then nothing can be lost.
HOW   — By Magitek power burned into his flesh, by the stolen might of the Warring Triad that lets him reshape the planet, by poison and betrayal and laughter — and by a nihilism so total it becomes its own dark divinity.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Why do people build things they know will one day be destroyed? Life — dreams — hope — I will destroy them all.

